<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12144d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12144d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12144d"> 144(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> SP slave</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Tout en bas de l&apos;&eacute;chelle sociale &eacute;taient les <i>fudirs</i>, esclaves proprement dits, &eacute;trangers, prisonniers de guerre, criminels qui avaient fui leur tribu d&apos;origine, simples fugitifs. Ils &eacute;taient autoris&eacute;s &agrave; vivre sur le territoire de la tribu, mais pouvaient en &ecirc;tre chass&eacute;s &agrave; tout moment. SP, pendent sa captivit&eacute;, appartint &agrave; cette classe des fudirs, il put en mesurer toute la lamentable situation. <br><font color="green">[14: Lowest of all in the social scale were the &ldquo;fudirs&rdquo; or real slaves, mostly strangers, prisoners of war, runaways, criminals and outlaws. They were allowed to live in the territory of the tribe, but might at any moment be expelled from it. <mark>St Patrick, during his captivity belonged to this class of &ldquo;fudirs&rdquo;</mark> and could well understand their wretched situation.]</font> <small> Riguet, Abb&eacute; <a name="RTSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RTSP"><cite title="source">Saint Patrice</cite></a> (1911) 16</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
